comment: West (IND) and Porter (WAS) make incidental contact with each other during Porter's off ball cut.
Stuckey (IND) does not affect Beal's (WAS) RSBQ as he attempts to go for the steal.
Miles (IND) makes contact with Wall's (WAS) arm and the contact affects his movement to the basket and layup attempt.
Gortat (WAS) and Hibbert (IND) engage during rebounding but neither player is in position to retrieve the rebound.
West (IND) makes incidental contact with Gortat (WAS) as he goes towards the basket for the offensive rebound.
Hill (IND) has his hand on Wall's (WAS) waist but does not affect his shot attempt.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that Gortat's (WAS) tip-in attempt occurred after the game clock had expired was upheld.
Stuckey (IND) makes foot to foot contact with Beal (WAS) that affects his ability to shoot the jump shot.
Porter (WAS) dislodges Miles (IND) on the alley-oop pass.
West (IND) sets the screen on Beal (WAS) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
Miles (IND) cleanly blocks Gortat's (WAS) layup attempt from behind. R-Slash shows that Miles' left arm is rested on Gortat's shoulder but it does not affect his shot attempt.
Stuckey (IND) does not affect Wall's (WAS) RSBQ in transition with the contact.
Porter (WAS) kicks the ball in the scrum for the loose ball.
After completing the handoff, there is no movement by Hibbert (IND) and Beal (WAS) runs into the screen.
Miles (IND) grabs Gortat's (WAS) arm and prevents him from rolling to the basket after setting a legal screen.
Gortat (WAS) cleanly strips the ball from Miles (IND) on the drive to the basket.
George (IND) inbounds the ball to Hill (IND) who first makes contact with the ball in the frontcourt before his momentum carries him into the backcourt.
There is no conclusive angle which shows if Miles (IND) touched the ball prior to it going OOB. Since there are more than 2 minutes remaining in OT, this play cannot be reviewed.
Gortat (WAS) slaps the backboard but it does not affect Hill's (IND) layup attempt.
Porter (WAS) dislodges Hibbert (IND) and affects his ability to retrieve the rebound.
West (IND) sets the screen on Porter (WAS) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
West (IND) makes contact with Gooden (WAS), but does not create space with a push.
Hibbert (IND) switches and moves his pivot foot as he makes his post move.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that the ball was last touched by Porter (WAS) was upheld and Indiana retained possession.
Hibbert (IND) jumps from point A to B and makes contact with Wall (WAS) on the successful layup attempt.
Gortat (WAS) makes incidental contact with West (IND) as he cuts down the lane.
West (IND) cleanly strips the ball from Beal (WAS) on the drive to the basket.
West (IND) grabs Porter's (WAS) arm and affects his ability to defend.
Gortat (WAS) sets the screen on Stuckey (IND) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
Stuckey (IND) and Gortat (WAS) make incidental contact with one another while going after the loose ball.
Gortat (WAS) grabs and holds Stuckey's (IND) arm and prevents him from getting out in transition.
Stuckey (IND) maintains legal guarding position while defending Beal's (WAS) drive to the basket.
Wall (WAS) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Hill (IND) in the backcourt.
Indiana does not advance the ball from the backcourt into the frontcourt during the allowed 8 seconds. Calling a timeout does not give a team a new 8 second count.
West (IND) makes incidental contact with Gortat (WAS) after he releases the ball that does not affect his layup attempt.
Beal (WAS) maintains legal guarding position while defending Miles' (IND) drive to the basket.
Gortat (WAS) sets the screen on Stuckey (IND) without giving him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction then grabs his arm and prevents him from defending the jump shot.
Hibbert (IND) pushes off Gortat (WAS) and affects his ability to defend.
Gortat (WAS) sets the screen on Miles (IND) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
Hibbert (IND) continues to move as he sets the screen, preventing Porter (WAS) from being able to take a foul.
Porter (WAS) commits a take foul on Hill (IND).
Butler (WAS) commits a take foul on West (IND).
Seraphin (WAS) sets the screen on Stuckey (IND) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
